---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base title="Predictive Software Delivery">

  <header class="hero">
    <span class="eyebrow">Software Agency</span>
    <h1>We ship software<br><em>you can predict.</em></h1>
    <p class="hero-subtext">Nolte replaces hourly billing with predictive delivery. You know what ships, when it ships, and what it costs — before we write a line of code.</p>
  </header>

  <div class="definition-block">
    <p>We are a software agency that bills for outcomes, not hours. Every engagement is forecast-driven, delivery-guaranteed, and backed by data.</p>
  </div>

  <section>
    <span class="section-label">What we do</span>
    <h2>Four things, done well</h2>
    <p>We focus on the work that moves the business. Everything we deliver is scoped, forecast, and guaranteed.</p>

    <div class="services-grid">
      <div class="service-cell">
        <span class="service-num">01</span>
        <h3>Product Engineering</h3>
        <p>Full-stack development for web and mobile products. We build, ship, and iterate — with every delivery tied to a business outcome.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="service-cell">
        <span class="service-num">02</span>
        <h3>Platform &amp; Infrastructure</h3>
        <p>Cloud architecture, CI/CD, observability, and runtime upgrades. Technical work with measurable impact on reliability and cost.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="service-cell">
        <span class="service-num">03</span>
        <h3>Data &amp; Integration</h3>
        <p>API design, third-party integrations, data pipelines, and migration. We connect your systems and make them talk to each other.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="service-cell">
        <span class="service-num">04</span>
        <h3>Strategy &amp; Advisory</h3>
        <p>Technical due diligence, architecture reviews, and roadmap planning. We help you make decisions before committing resources.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <span class="section-label">Our model</span>
    <h2>Predictive, not hourly</h2>
    <p>Traditional agencies sell time. We sell deliveries — discrete, validated units of work tied to business outcomes. Every delivery is forecast using historical throughput data, so you know what to expect before we start.</p>
    <p>This means no surprise invoices. No ambiguous updates. Just a clear picture of what ships, when, and what it costs.</p>
  </section>

  <div class="cta-block">
    <h2>See how the model works</h2>
    <p>Learn what counts as a delivery and why it matters.</p>
    <a class="cta-btn" href="/delivery">Read the Model</a>
  </div>

  <div class="bottom-line">
    <h2>Software delivery should be predictable.</h2>
    <p>You would not accept unpredictable timelines and costs from any other vendor. Your software partner should be no different.</p>
    <p style="margin-top: 1rem;">We built Nolte around one idea: if you define what done means before you start, you can forecast it, guarantee it, and prove it.</p>
  </div>

</Base>
